## Contracts

### NFTCollection (ERC-721)

The collection contract supports:

- **Minting** with auto-incrementing token IDs and a configurable mint price
- **Max supply** cap to limit the total number of tokens
- **Base URI** for IPFS metadata resolution
- **Full ERC-721 compliance** including `safeTransferFrom` with `onERC721Received` callback
- **ERC-165** interface detection
- **Owner withdrawal** of accumulated mint proceeds

### Marketplace

The marketplace contract supports:

- **List items** - Token owners can list their NFTs at a fixed price
- **Buy items** - Anyone can purchase a listed NFT by sending the listing price
- **Cancel listings** - Sellers can remove their listings at any time
- **Make offers** - Buyers can make offers on any NFT (funds held in escrow)
- **Accept offers** - Token owners can accept any active offer
- **Withdraw offers** - Offerers can reclaim their escrowed funds
- **Platform fee** - 2.5% fee on all sales, withdrawable by the contract owner

### Royalty (EIP-2981)

The royalty contract supports:

- **Default royalty** - A global royalty percentage applied to all tokens
- **Per-token overrides** - Individual tokens can have custom royalty settings
- **Max cap** - Royalties are capped at 10% to protect buyers
- **ERC-165** interface detection for the EIP-2981 standard

## Metadata Format

NFT metadata follows the standard JSON format:

```json
{
  "name": "My NFT #1",
  "description": "An awesome NFT from my collection",
  "image": "ipfs://YOUR_IMAGE_CID",
  "attributes": [
    { "trait_type": "Background", "value": "Blue" },
    { "trait_type": "Rarity", "value": "Common" }
  ]
}
```

Upload metadata to IPFS using the provided script, then set the base URI on the collection contract.

## Testing

Run the full test suite:

```bash
forge test -vvv
```

Tests cover:

- Minting and token ID auto-increment
- Transfers (regular and safe)
- Approvals and operator management
- Token URI generation
- Marketplace listing, buying, and cancellation
- Offer creation, acceptance, and withdrawal
- Platform fee calculations
- Royalty calculations with default and per-token overrides

